```java
    @Column(nullable = false)
    @Lob
    @Column(columnDefinition = "LONGTEXT")
    private String content;
 ```

This change will:

1. Use @Lob to indicate this is a Large Object
2. Set the column type to LONGTEXT in MySQL which can store up to 4GB of text
3. Prevent the data truncation error when saving large content
You'll need to update your database schema accordingly. You can use this SQL:

```sql
ALTER TABLE fs_posts MODIFY COLUMN content LONGTEXT;
 ```

